						               													<description>Super Smart (or Supersmart) is a game for 2-4 players from 9 years and up.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In this game you are are answering questions in one word beginning with a specific, but random letter.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The board consist with four independent lanes from each with a &amp;quot;Start&amp;quot; field and a passage of extra 10 steps. In the middle there is a roulette with letters (and small numbers) and six (6) coloured spots; Four (4) red ones and two (2) green ones. The game also contains four (4) player pawns (Red, Green, Blue and Yellow), one (1) die (Red with golden eyes) and a deck of Question Cards (from now called CQs).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The CQs are suffled and placed face down in reach of all players.&amp;#10;The youngest player starts the game by pushing the arrow of the roulette and there are following three possibility:&amp;#10;1) If the arrow stops at a letter the player takes a CQ and read up the question for the player on the right, who answer the question with a word starting with the letter from the roulette. The amount of time that you have to reply is agreed before the game starts. If the answer is approved the player is allowed to move one (1) step up the ladder - if not the player is not moving.&amp;#10;After this all other players roll the die - the player who first roll the number under the letter, can also move his/her pawn one (1) step up the ladder&amp;#10;2) Destiny / Red field - if the arrow stops here, all players roll the die and the player who rolls the number shown on the roulette will move his/her pawn one (1) step down the ladder.&amp;#10;3) Luck / Green field - If the arrow stops here, the player who spins the wheel can move his/her pawn two (2) steps up the ladder.&amp;#10;If the arrow stops between two fields, the player do a respin.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The first to reach the top of the ladder is the winner!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
